Since the purchases of a property had to undertake the debts with which it was encumbered, Mommsen explains the word, with great probability, in reference to the percentage which was deducted from the price of a property, in consideration of its being saddled with debts. Thus purchasers who, instead of the full price, offered 50 per cent. of the price, would justly bc called ‘ cutters off ' (sectores). The property of Milo, for instance, on account of its indebtedness, was sold semuncia, i.e. for ,ch of its value.
